dynamicStorage

Class GameInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • dynamicStorage.GameInfo
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class GameInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class holds all of the information needed to create or load a game and is constantly updated throughout game play. This class is serialized into a save file every time that the game is saved.
    Author:
    Stanton Parham (stparham@ncsu.edu)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

        Creates a new GameInfo object with the passed in saveSlot number, playerName, and difficulty; Generates a new random game map; Sets timeElapsed to 0; Sets score to 0; Sets resource values and resource max values to class constant values;
        Parameters:
        saveSlot - the save slot in which this GameInfo object will be saved (1, 2, or 3)
        playerName - the name of the player for this game
        difficulty - a String representing the difficulty of the game
